Build a Flow in Data Cloud

Automate your business process and launch a flow internally when a data record changes. A flow collects data and performs actions in Salesforce or an external system.

REQUIRED EDITIONS
Available in: Lightning Experience
From Setup, in the Quick Find box, enter Flows, and then select Flows.
Click New Flow.
Select Platform Event - Triggered Flow, and then click Create.
A platform event-triggered flow runs when an event message is received.
For the platform event, select Data Object Data Change Event.
Click Add Element, and then click Create Records.
Enter the label and API name for your record.
Select Use separate resources, and literal values.
From the Object dropdown, select your custom object.
Set the field values for your custom object, and then click Done.
Click Save.
Enter the flow label and flow API name.
Click Save.

After you build a flow, activate it by clicking Activate.
